{"TopicId":141546,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Apparent diameters of celestial bodies in KSP","CreatedByName":"NovaSilisko","CreatedById":3897,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T07:15:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"NovaSilisko","CreatedById":3897,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T07:15:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo! I\u0027ve been thinking about doing this for a while. I made a chart showing how big various celestial bodies would look from the surface of Kerbin, compared to many real world bodies viewed from Earth:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(click for full size)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.redd.it/zbl4dblusb2x.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022LmGHEKDpgYJHpG7JqRoE1RsXC9UnYbUbWpKKpVe6\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.redditmedia.com/LmGHEKDpgYJHpG7JqRoE1RsXC9UnYbUbWpKKpVe6uS4.jpg?w=1024\u0026amp;s=4449d420dac68094192db84604a2b3e2\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook up at the moon outside, and imagine it being almost four times bigger. That\u0027s about what it would look like.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBonus: Ike when viewed from Duna is \u003Cem\u003Einsane: \u003C/em\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/AYqokIx.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://i.imgur.com/AYqokIx.jpg\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-10T07:16:08Z\u0022 title=\u002206/10/2016 07:16  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 10, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by NovaSilisko\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T07:24:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222624846\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141546\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465542905\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00223897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NovaSilisko\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, NovaSilisko said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBonus: Ike when viewed from Duna is \u003Cem\u003Einsane: \u003C/em\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/AYqokIx.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://i.imgur.com/AYqokIx.jpg\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReminds me of that \u0022what if the Moon orbited as close as the ISS\u0022 video animation... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GluttonyReaper","CreatedById":59429,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T08:18:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRelevant:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/eB32ykkiJk8?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T10:13:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice, nice, but what about sun/Kerbol/ball of plasma?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222624886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141546\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465546704\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259429\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GluttonyReaper\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, GluttonyReaper said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRelevant:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/eB32ykkiJk8?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsomeone should make the same with KSP, with Mun replaced by other bodies.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T10:24:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have often said the Kerbol system is adorable!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom each of the moons of\u00A0Jool you\u00A0can clearly each of the other moons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love the fun-size solar system!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-10T10:27:29Z\u0022 title=\u002206/10/2016 10:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 10, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Brainlord Mesomorph\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"moogoob","CreatedById":118251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T17:36:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice visualization!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T17:41:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuper cool, man.\u00A0 Thank you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NovaSilisko","CreatedById":3897,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-11T05:08:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn a little while I\u0027m going to calculate the views from the various moons of Jool, I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cantab","CreatedById":104935,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-11T13:33:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s made me realise how lousy 1080p, coupled with a possibly shrunk field of view, is. If Minmus were in the real sky its flats would be plainly visible, but in KSP it\u0027s usually a single pixel or two.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-11T13:50:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222626485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141546\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465652035\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104935\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cantab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, cantab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s made me realise how lousy 1080p, coupled with a possibly shrunk field of view, is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs somebody for who CGA was an amazing upgrade in graphic capabilities, I beg to differ. 2K is really not that bad.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The_Rocketeer","CreatedById":81727,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-11T14:02:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222626485\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141546\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465652035\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104935\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cantab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, cantab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s made me realise how lousy 1080p, coupled with a possibly shrunk field of view, is. If Minmus were in the real sky its flats would be plainly visible, but in KSP it\u0027s usually a single pixel or two.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n^^ Justification for actual KSP telescopes.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut then again, according to this graphic we should be able to see detail of Mars\u0027 surface from Earth, which even with Hubble isn\u0027t/wasn\u0027t very sharp.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nHST Mars:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/full_width_feature/public/thumbnails/image/hs-2005-34-j-full_jpg.jpg?itok=4wi_1dCA\u0022 alt=\u0022hs-2005-34-j-full_jpg.jpg?itok=4wi_1dCA\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-11T14:09:39Z\u0022 title=\u002206/11/2016 02:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by The_Rocketeer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NovaSilisko","CreatedById":3897,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-11T19:16:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222626505\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141546\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465653739\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002281727\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The_Rocketeer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, The_Rocketeer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut then again, according to this graphic we should be able to see detail of Mars\u0027 surface from Earth, which even with Hubble isn\u0027t/wasn\u0027t very sharp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really, as I said in the notes in the image, anything under about 70 arcseconds apparent diameter is going to be basically indistinguishable from a point, and Mars falls well below that limit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The_Rocketeer","CreatedById":81727,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-11T23:16:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI didn\u0027t mean to suggest that the graphic was inaccurate or misinformative. I was making some sort of point that I no longer seem to fully grasp. Guess it just wasn\u0027t that important!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nNice pic! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Delfinus","CreatedById":154315,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-13T02:42:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I think the fact that Eve is above the 70 arcsecond limit is pretty cool, if you lived on Kerbin you\u0027d be able to look up, and see another planet, sitting up there in the sky, that\u0027d be pretty beautiful, even if it\u0027d appear pretty small.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-13T02:43:13Z\u0022 title=\u002206/13/2016 02:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DolphinDude3\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}